Energy Empowerment is one of the main partner of Boikanyo Group (www.boikanyogroup.com)

IMAGO Engineering is a company for the construction of fully automated plants that produce protein, fat and fertilizers from insects based on high effective bioreactor system for 3 main purposes: 
- to feed the planet; 
- to green the deserts;
- to fight global warming.

Компанията е регистрирана през 1989г., като постепенно се развива и разраства, разширявайки обхвата на своята дейност. Целият инвестиционен портфейл е обединен през 2007г. чрез създаване на холдинговата структура БУЛАГРО ГРУП ХОЛДИНГ ЕАД.

БУЛАГРО развива своята дейност в следните направления:

 БУЛАГРО АД - търговия с продукти за растителна защита и торове, хибридни семена, селскостопански застраховки, услуги, агроконсултации. Разполага с най-голямата aгроаптека в региона на Стара Загора;

 БУЛАГРО МАШИНИ АД - многогодишно присъствие в агро сектора с продажба и пълно сервизно обслужване на селскостопанска техника на световни лидери, сред които Poettinger, Hardi, Bogballe, Dominoni, Mascar, Einboeck. Изградената търговска и сервизна мрежа покрива цялата страна;

 БУЛОЙЛ ЕООД - доставка на гориво и смазочни материали за селскостопанска техника;

 БУЛАГРО ЗЕМЯ ЕООД - създадена през месец април 2007г. с основна цел арендуване на земя за изпитвания на нови технологии, семена, производствени опити и тестове. През 2013 г. в базата на компанията в старозагорското село Яздач заработи и модерен завод за заготовка на семена за посев, оборудван с машини от най-висок клас.

AAGI gives Australian growers an opportunity to be world leaders in analytics-driven decision making to drive efficiency and precision and support farm enterprise risk management.

The initiative will deliver grower-facing analytics technologies and work with GRDC RD&E partners and other stakeholders to improve Australian grains research, development and extension (RD&E) outcomes.

AAGI’s mission is to use analytics on grains data to help Australian grain growers to be more profitable and globally competitive through:

Supporting GRDC’s RD&E portfolio with good, efficient, analytics;
Doing more upskilling of the grains RD&E workforce;
Giving grains RD&E more analytics options;
Investing more in high-priority analytics research;
Attracting more co-investment and/or revenue to support grains RD&E analytics.
AAGI is an investment of the Grains Research and
Development Corporation (GRDC). It is led by strategic partners
Curtin University, the University of Queensland and the
University of Adelaide.

— A Brazilian-German Vision to Foster the Sustainable Use of Local Biodiversity in the Bioeconomy  —

AcroAlliance is an applied project that involves research and industry partners from Brazil and Germany, with expertise from the macaúba seed (Acrocomia aculeata, macaw palm) to advanced applications. 

The goal of AcroAlliance is to develop high value refined oils, proteins and dietary fibers from acrocomia fruits, while addressing major gaps for the development of a sustainable acrocomia value web. 

Specific objectives are:

• developing optimum planting material; 
• determining best agricultural practices for integrated Macauba land-use systems; 
• provide a validated postharvest treatment to ensure high quality fractions;
• developing and optimizing processes to obtain refined oils, proteins and dietary fibers within a decentralized biorefinery concept
• evaluating the market potential and technical feasibility of the developed Macauba-based products; 
• identifying sustainable strategies and scenarios for implementing the value web concept.

AgConnect is a vibrant network of farmers, business owners, service providers and county government, that connects farmers to business resources, training, and financing to grow business and promoting smart, sustainable agricultural economic development, as well as consumers to local farmers for food security and educational resources about agriculture. 

AgConnect is a vibrant network of farmers, business owners, service providers and county government, that connects farmers to business resources, training, and financing to grow business and promoting smart, sustainable agricultural economic development, as well as consumers to local farmers for food security and educational resources about agriculture. 

This public/private partnership is the successor to the county's Ag Council, and was the foremost recommendation of the 2022 Chester County Agricultural Economic Development Strategic Plan.

AgConnect, is now an initiative of Chester County and the Chester County Economic Development Council, and serves Berks, Bucks, Chester, Delaware, Montgomery and Philadelphia Counties. 

This organization is run by the Advisory Executive Board, a diverse and experienced committee that oversees the development and execution of AgConnect’s workplan, ensuring alignment with the county’s strategic objectives.

To address various aspects of agricultural development, four action teams have been formed:
•AgWorks: Workforce development team focused on regional agricultural workforce development;
•AgFunds: Financial team dedicated to providing farm loan opportunities and financial support;
•AgDoes: Chester County team tasked with implementing the Agricultural Economic Development Plan for the county;
•AgSpeaks: Promotions team responsible for promoting the agricultural industry, coordinating the Farm Guide, and organizing the Chester County Farmer of the Year ceremony.

En 2017, Augusto & Malka est né d’un partenariat entre deux familles et deux pays – José Luís Augusto, ingénieur de cacao sao tomien et Sacha Malka, spécialiste en agroforesterie tropicale français. Ensemble, nous avons pour but de construire des systèmes agricoles qui respectent tant la nature que les hommes, pour produire de façon durable les meilleurs produits tropicaux. Pour relever ce défi, nous avons trois principes fondateurs :

Un système qui réplique la forêt tropicale, soit l’agroforesterie ;
Zéro pesticides et zéro fertilisants de synthèse ;
Une production transparente destinée tant au marché local qu’international.
In 2017, Augusto & Malka was born from a partnership between two families and two countries – José Luís Augusto, a Sao Tomean cocoa engineer and Sacha Malka, a French tropical agroforestry specialist. Together, we aim to build agricultural systems that respect both nature and people, to produce the best tropical products in a sustainable way. To meet this challenge, we have three founding principles:

A system that replicates the rainforest, which is agroforestry;
Zero pesticides and zero synthetic fertilizers;
Transparent production for both local and international markets.

We facilitate decision-making discussions for leaders, teams, and organizations that want to create sustaining success.  We:
*engage with organizations in developing and implementing strategic & action plans;  
*design and facilitate agendas for stakeholders to engage with each other on big-picture, future-focused opportunities and challenges through Think Tanks, Executive Conferences, and Summits; 
*Conduct training and workshops;
*Speaking on topics related to the future of food and agriculture; leadership development-youth and professionals; strategic planning; and action plan implementation.
